```

If you prefer to bypass upstream `Makefile` fragility entirely (recommended for Go RPMs), replace the `%build` block with:

```spec
%build
export GOPROXY=off
go build -trimpath -ldflags "-s -w" -o %{name} . ./cmd/...
```

This directly invokes the Go toolchain, avoids missing Makefile targets, and matches standard openSUSE Go packaging practice. Rebuild after applying.
